 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Written at Camberwell, near London, in the Study of Mr. Wainwright, now Baron of the Exchequer in Ireland, where the Author accidentally din'd alone.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">happily I pass my Hours</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In  delightful Bow'rs;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From thence the beauteous Walks survey;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or thro' the fragrant Mazes stray;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or o'er the Study cast my Eye,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where , and  lie,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Just Emblem of a Bosom grac'd</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With Law, and Elegance of Taste;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I invoke in vain,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">answers with Disdain:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">", you're here allow'd to roam.</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"And bid to think yourself at home:</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"O'er the Domesticks then preside;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Let that content your Female Pride;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"In vain you call on me To-day;</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Here  only I obey.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
